column28: but let me first just say that this is the worst SW film of all time. It\'s even worse than Attack of the Clones. Yes
column29:
really.

The movie itself is shot well and is visually fantastic. The sound effects and soundtrack are on point. That\'s basically all this movie has going for it. I literally only signed up for Rotten Tomatoes so I could review this movie. I am a life-long SW fan and own all of the movies
column30: played basically all of the video games
column31:
and I have also read dozens of the books. I am a bit of a super fan you could say.

TLJ suffers from a number of problems. There are serious plot holes
column32: plot elements which simply do not make sense
column33: failed attempts at humor that come off as immersion-breaking rather than genuinely funny
column34: and oh so much social/political pandering. Every woman in the movie is a strong
column35: brave badass leader type and pretty much all of the men are bumbling idiots or totally evil. I don\'t care that the movie ran long
column36: but what I do care about is that a lot of what is in the movie is utterly pointless and doesn\'t serve to further the plot. The character development in this film is basically non-existent. You learn absolutely nothing whatsoever about Snoke before he is killed. NOTHING! You learn nothing about Rey aside from the fact that her parents were poor nobodies
column37:
yet she is able to knock Jedi Master Luke Skywalker to the ground in a duel and master basically everything she attempts to do with virtually no training whatsoever. The existing Star Wars storyline before Disney bought Lucas out was fantastic and could have provided material for dozens of movies taking place after the original trilogy and even thousands of years before and everywhere inbetween. Disney rendered almost all of it non-canon and now we are left with a lukewarm bowl of poop soup.

I could go on and on and on detailing every stupid thing wrong with this movie but I am sure those points have been mentioned countless times by other reviewers. I\'ll sum it up like this:


PROS:
-great visuals
-great sound/soundtrack
-old school puppet Yoda
-some good battle scenes both in space and lightsaber duels


CONS:
-terrible character decisions make by Disney / Johnson
-weak dialogue
-no character development at all
-numerous inane plot holes
-pointless quests that people go on that just waste screen time
-sociopolitical pandering
-feminist agenda b.s.
-new uses of the Force never seen before that simply do not make sense
-some parts were very confusing and didn\'t make sense
-classic characters like R2D2
